This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to reading comprehension and numerical reasoning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a BERT-based model, which is a popular deep learning architecture for natural language processing, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. The paper also involves training and optimizing the model, indicating cs.LG (Learning) as a possible category. The use of neural networks and the focus on improving performance on a specific dataset suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves image processing to extract information from math word problems, which could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
